               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Śǝrʿāta qǝddāse “Ordinary of the Mass” (fols. 3r-31v)
 II)
                     Anaphoras (fols. 31v-110r)
 II-1) Anaphora of the Apostles (fols. 31va
                     l.12–41vb l.17)
 II-2) Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ (fols. 42ra l.1-
                     45vb l.5), preceded by the “Testament that Jesus Christ told…”
 II-3)
                     Anaphora of Our Lady by St Cyriacus of Behnesa (fols. 45va l.6-52vb l.10)
                     II-4) Anaphora of St John, son of Thunder (fols. 53ra l.1–59vb l.8)
 II-5)
                     Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox Fathers of Nicaea (fols. 59va l.11–65vb l.27),
                     preceded by the Nicene Creed (Ṣalota haymanot)
 II-6) Anaphora of St
                     Athanasius (fols. 66ra l.3–72vb l.15)
 II-7) Anaphora of St Basil of
                     Cesarea, followed by Śǝrʿāta bäwiʾotä qǝddāse zähośaʾǝna (fols. 73ra l.4–79vb
                     l.15)
 II-8) Anaphora of St Gregory of Nyssa (fols. 80ra l.1- 84vb
                     l.19)
 II-9) Anaphora of St Epiphanius (fols. 85ra l.1–90rb l.20)
                     II-10) Anaphora of St John Chrysostom (fols. 90va l.1– 95vb l.4)
 II-11)
                     Anaphora of St Cyril of Alexandria (fols. 95ra l.10–99vb l.24)
 II-12)
                     Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug (fols. 100ra l.4– 104rb l.18)
 II-13)
                     Anaphora of St Dioscorus (fols. 104va l.1-107rb l.22)
 II-14) The Second
                     Anaphora of St Gregory (fols. 107va l.1–110rb l.18)
 III) Daily Office
                     Prayers and Litanies (fols. 112r-123r)
 
 Additiones 1-2.</summary>
