                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#123rb">f. 123rb</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> The note mentions that the Ms. has been donated to
                           Qarsabar Mikāʾel in 1966 A.M. (= 1973/74 A.D.) by wayzaro<note> Bǝrritu.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#123v">f. 123v</locus>
                           <desc>: Purchase note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> Hardly readable. The note mentions that wayzaro
                           Bǝrritu paid for the M<locus target="#110">110</locus>
                           <note> Birr, in 1966 A.M. (= 1973/74 A.D.). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- <locus target="#2v">2v</locus>: Table of contents
                           precedes the texts, with the titles of the texts and their ordinal
                           numbers (the pages are not indicated). In the table of contents the
                           Anaphoras go first, followed by Śǝrʿāta qǝddāse, while in the Ms. itself
                           the order is vice versa.
 - <locus target="#4r">4r</locus>, 13v, 14r,
                           17v, 20v, 22v, 35r, 60r, 61r, 80r, 85r, 104v: Notes in the upper
                           margin.
 - <locus target="#29v">29v</locus>. Note in the bottom
                           margin.
 - <locus target="#12rb">12rb</locus>, 41vb, 52vb, 72va,
                           72vb, 79rb, 79va, 84vb, 90rb, 99vb, 107rb, 110v: Lists of masculine and
                           feminine personal names, only partly coincide with one another.
 -
                           Running titles appear throughout the Ms. in the upper margins.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
